  "concept": "vuejs/core#9877: `defineProps` cannot declared generic boolean type",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:23:18.408947+00:00",
  "text": "`defineProps` cannot declared generic boolean type\n\n### Vue version\n\n3.3.4\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://play.vuejs.org/#\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nSee vue playground, the compiled prop result\n\n### What is expected?\n\nthe compiled prop `m` should be `{ type: Boolean }`\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\nthe compiled prop `m` is `{}`\n\n### System Info\n\n_No response_\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\n_No response_",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "scope: script-setup",
    "🔩 p2-edge-case"
  ],
